data.description: Experience tranquil waterfront living at its finest in this spectacular property nestled at the mouth of Dog River offering quick access to the river, Dauphin Island, and Mobile Bay down to the Gulf of Mexico.  Architecturally designed by Mike McLeod and custom-built in 2008, this island-style coastal cottage offers unparalleled access to nature while being located just minutes from I-10, I-65, downtown Mobile, Buccaneer and Mobile yacht clubs, restaurants, retail shops, and entertainment.  Boasting breathtaking views of the marsh, river, and abundant protected wildlife, this sailor's paradise provides deep water access for boat dockage, making it ideal for water enthusiasts. Entertaining is effortless with the open-concept light filled living area and seamless indoor-outdoor flow onto the covered wrap-around porches.  The gourmet kitchen is a chef's dream, featuring custom cabinetry, granite countertops, high-end stainless-steel appliances, breakfast bar, and dining room.  Recently replaced refrigerator, washer, and dryer convey with the property.  With two bedrooms and two full baths on each level (including renovated bathrooms), every inch of this home exudes comfort and style. Generously sized bedrooms offer access to the porches, while a third-floor observation loft provides panoramic views of the river and Mobile Bay. The loft has windows on all sides, and is ideal for a workout, reading, music, art, etc.  Relish in the serenity of sunrise and sunset from the expansive porches, listening to the sounds and beauty of nature. Elevated 16.3 feet above high tide and offering covered parking for four cars, this meticulously maintained property is ready for you to call home. Don't miss out on this rare opportunity to own a piece of paradise.  All updates per the seller. Listing company makes no representation as to accuracy of square footage; buyer to verify.
